content.description: This climb has fun, well protected, slab climbing.
content.protection: 8 bolts to chain and ring anchors.
content.location: Start up and right from the belay area.

content.description: This mixed route climbs a well protected but exposed arete with great holds that keep you on the edge all the way to the anchors.
content.protection: A set of 4 cams; # 2, 1, .75, & .75, sew up the start.  Six bolts lead up the arete to chains.  When you pull the rope it can get stuck on the flakes below the first bolt.  To avoid this, pull way to the right with a good hard tug.
content.location: Climb the distinctive arete via a fun, 5.7 crack start.  Hike left across the base and carefully scramble up to gain the crack.

content.description: Scramble onto the big detached flake to clip the first bolt.  Thin moves off the flake gain the second bolt.  Well protected but tricky slab mantles lead to the anchors.
content.location: Starts off the large detached flake at the base of the slab.

content.description: This small West facing dome sits above the town of Catalina, North of Tucson.  The routes are in the shade through the morning.  Although it's close to town, climbing at this dome has a distinct wilderness feel.
